descript.abstract: The shape and orientation of the ground floor of all structures in a local government. This information is typically compiled from orthoimagery or other aerial photography sources. This representation of the building footprints support the local government basemaps. It also serves as a source for public works, public safety, planning and other agencies that are responsible for the active management of site addresses, facilities, and land use information.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: The base elevation of the building
The user who performed the last update
The height of the building eave
The direction (azimuth) of the roof ridge line or roof face in case of shed
The date the feature was last updated in the maintenance database
The number of floors above ground level
